<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="855" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/2010¼</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary
                                    of State</gloss> to the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Murray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-23">October 23, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Murray</hi>: I have read with interest your
                            memorandum of October 15 relative to the President’s idea that possibly
                            Palestine should be handled on a trusteeship basis. He also mentioned
                            that to me once briefly in conversation. I am inclined to think that
                            detailed consideration of this should await the Secretary’s return, but
                            in the meantime I shall, if I have an opportunity, attempt to get from
                            the President more background on his thinking on this.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>